Step 1: Identify the quick assets. These include cash on hand, bank deposits, accounts receivable, and interest receivable. Do not include inventory.

Step 2: List the relevant figures as of the end date (2024-02-05):  
• Cash on Hand: 3,041,599.18  
• Bank Deposits: 1,103,978.40  
• Interest Receivable: 13,555.89  
• Accounts Receivable: 10,537,836.59  

Step 3: Calculate total quick assets:  
Total Quick Assets = 3,041,599.18 + 1,103,978.40 + 13,555.89 + 10,537,836.59 = 14,696,970.06

Step 4: Identify the current liabilities as of the end date (2024-02-05):  
• Total Current Liabilities = 1,903,121.89

Step 5: Calculate the Quick Ratio:  
Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
Quick Ratio = 14,696,970.06 / 1,903,121.89 ≈ 7.72

Thus, the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 7.72.
